s Insist\nProsperity Near.\nThe Republican tom-tom of pros\nperity was beaten at twenty-four\nward and precinct rallies Wednes\nday night by county organization\norators and candidates.\nArchibald M. Hall, candidate for\nrepresentative, speaking at 931 West\nThirty-first street, said:\n\u2018Statements of leading economists\nand bankers indicate that every\nj thing is set for a rapid business\nrecovery.\u201d\nRecounting the achievements of\nthe Hoover administration thus far,\nJames M. Ogden, state attorney\ngeneral, speaking at Odd Fellow\u2019s\nHall, East Washington street and\nHamilton avenue said that \u201cthe re\nmarkable record of the accomplish\nments of the Hoover administration\nseems almost impossible -when we\nconsider the obstacles with which\nthat administration has had to con\ntend.\n\u201cThe great value of these ac\ncomplishments is being felt more\nand more and Republican victory\nthis fall will speed up conditions\ngenerally while Democratic success\nwould longer delay this much\nneeded recovery.\u201d\nThe European Exhibit\nREVELATION\nNow in Indianapolis\n203-205 W. WASHINGTON\nFOrf ADULTS ONLY\nFEATURING\nMax Heims Preserved Specimens\nfrom Hamburg, Germany.\nV// DANCE TONIGHT\nf// 35c Before 8:30 \\1\nJOIN THE GOLD RUSH II\nTONIGHT ALSO JIB\nHit Instruction* on Advanced IgS\nDancing 7:45-9:00 P. M. //M\n|3\u00a7L\\ JAC BRODERICK and f/Mt\nAMUSEMENTS\nENGLISH THEATREI\nTWO NITES\u2014SAT. MAT.\nOCT. 31\u2014 NOV. 1 j\nf 1 yi\nr\nm*sg& (wtffWMffii)\nk^mmwrn\nI Nights oOc-$l .00 -$1.50-$2.00-$2.50 1\nAlatinee 50c-SI.OO-$1.50-$2.00 I\nMail Orders Now \u2014Seats Monday B\nNEARS END OF PROBE\nOF OIL FRAUD CHARGE\nAttorney-General Aid to Report in\nFederal Lands Case.\nWASHINGTON. Oct. 23.\u2014Seth W.\nRichardsor, assistant attorney-gen\neral in charge of public Ipnd mat\nters, expects to complete his investi\ngation tnis week of the charges\nbrought against the interior depart\nment in the handling of oil shale\nlands in Colorado by Ralph S.\nKelley, former chief of the field di\nvision in Denver.\nKelley has concluded his series of\nfourteen copyrighted newspaper\narticles attacking the interior de\npartment on grounds of alleged\nfavoritism to applicants. In them\nhe assailed Dr. Hubert Work of\nColorado, former secretary of the\ninterior; Dr. Ray Lyman Wilbur,\npresent secretary; E. C. Finney, de\npartment solicitor and first assistant\nsecretary under Works and others.\nMOTION PICTURES\nAnd Then\u2014\nWhat happens when a\nLubitsch\u2019s romance\nthat\u2019* spicier even than\n\"MONTIF CARLO\u201d\nJEANETTE 1 MacDONALQ\nJACK BUCHANAN\ni 7or>vo rrouj\nN Qi/\\NA H\nAMUSEMENTS\nAnother Great Show Starts\nhi\u2022] F<4 SATURDAY\na H K A I the way to a \u201cL seats\nInIuiIHBBAjSigSHBMBM lifetime of love and\n\u2014i thrills. i:0o 7SC\nDON\u2019T MISS THIS BULL F M\nThe whole town id talking\nabont Its fine entertainment. MBfti\u00df\u00dfgM\u00dfftL i CU/IC\nTODAY and TOMORROW ffPSffePR LLWIO\n\u2014l.ast Two Days\u2014 _ r\u2014 C*\nEdmund SWIM, AYR^S\nLowe and I; :pm Qt?iKT O ON TOE\nJoan Bennett in 3|l WESTERN\n\u201cCrnTl AND FRONT\u201d in anew\nw and mart'elous role.\nYARD\u2019\u2019 i' \u2713fSj vug\nStrange I>ovc Adventure 5 Yr\n6 ACTS'RKO 6\nVAUDEVILLE\nWILL HIGGIE and GIRLS jFffl O 1 1\nSIX GALENOS O jl\nCHERRY, JUNE and- w\nSTAGE SHOW SI ACT3 j\nABANDON OCEAN\nFLIGHT TO U. S.\nColumbia Fliers Instead to\nMake Tour of Europe.\nBv United Press\nLONDON, Oct. 23.\u2014Pressure\nbrought by United States Ambassa\ndor Charles G. Dawes, the Canadian\nauthorities and others resulted in a\ndecision today by Captain J. Errol\nBoyd and Lieutenant Harry Connor,\ntrans-Atlantic aviators, to abandon\ntheir plan to fiy the monoplane Co\nlumbia back to the North American\ncontinent.\nInstead, they plan to leave the\nend of the week on a flight around\nEurope, and will take a steamship\nback to America some time early in\nNovember.\n\u201cWe received many letters asking\nus not to fly home because of the\nrisk,\u201d Captain Boyd said. \u201cPremier\nBennett of Canada and Ambassador\nDawes also advised us not to fly.\nLAST \u201cThose 3 French Girls\u201d\n2 with FIFI DORSAY\u2014CLIFF EDWARDS\nand REGINALD DENNY\nDAYS Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer All Talking Picture I\nne l>ay Mo Last Da.. W\nchevalier I Walter f 4 Marx I\n81/1ifM81...... \u2018boy or I HUSTON I Brothers\nBh i ffgPARIS.** I M in\n(m Hi Pln Charlie Davis' 8 \u201cANIMAL 9\nf w\nSSAS.iI\n*1 I '^mSSn\nMONTE UHL\nCARLO\" eKEj\nPARAMOUNT\u2019S gay adventure with If v\nJEANETTE MacDONALD I.\nWrMfflk V s\nMoSiuaicl l\neverybody: Meet de Kingfish;\ne imous Frcshair Taxi. Attend\n:lrUon of the Mystic Knights of\nII LAST COMKDV SENSATION OF THE TEAR DON\u2019T I\nTWO \u201cUP THE RIVER\u201d MISS\nI DAYS Warren Hymer\u2014Spencer Tracy IT!\nPl|||||Pj STARTING SATURDAY\ntom-boy of the irrmi a- the Ilf.- of the\nhotte.t party ever m rrfnH: \u2018\u25a0h\" tt .'ll.'\nM Gold Digger\nr&fgg of Broadway li titjjk Bw lmJgr\nV Prospecting in MW W IT,\nW Havana. Faster p p m v\n\u201cGold Diggers of y&P WINNIE\nBroadway.\u201d She /NFIIGHTNER.\nWrote the Chap- IRENE DfcLROV\nWhnineF* he JACK WHUINO\nH P CHAftLLS 2VTTBACRIX\nALSO. KM W BOCKNE SERIES\n\u201cSo we decided we had better not.\nWe booked passage on the Duchess\nof Richmond, intending to go home\nin a %afe and sane way. sailing Oct.\n31. However, we now are goihg on\na tour of Europe in the old Colum\nbia We expect to sail for home\nNov\\_7 or Nov. 14,\u201d\nMOTION PICTURES\nOCT. 23, 1930","height":"26499","width":"19239"}}
